      • HorizontalListView_dividerWidth

        public static final int HorizontalListView_dividerWidth

        This symbol is the offset where the R.attr.dividerWidth attribute's value can be found in the HorizontalListView array.

        Must be a dimension value, which is a floating point number appended with a unit such as "14.5sp". Available units are: px (pixels), dp (density-independent pixels), sp (scaled pixels based on preferred font size), in (inches), mm (millimeters).

        This may also be a reference to a resource (in the form "@[package:]type:name") or theme attribute (in the form "?[package:][type:]name") containing a value of this type.
